comments.body:
`dt-header` is pretty important. 

1. What error do the tests give?
2. The library requires 2.3, so there's no way you can use it with 2.1, so I don't think there's any point

The other rules are not that important, but there's value in having a tslint.json with no overrides, because we run scripts over Definitely Typed occasionally, and those scripts often have to skip packages with overrides since they don't follow the normal rules. So I'd prefer to have all 3 overrides gone.

The usual way to get around `prefer-const` is to make your unitialised variables into parameters instead:

```ts
let x: number;
g(x)
// =>
function f(x: number) {
  g(x)
}
```
